<h1>CS2 Trade Up Breakeven Calculator</h1>
<p>The breakeven point is the minimum expected value a trade up must have to avoid losing money on average. Understanding breakeven helps you quickly filter out unprofitable trade ups and focus on opportunities worth pursuing.</p>

<h2>Calculating Breakeven</h2>
<p>The breakeven formula is simple: <strong>Breakeven EV = Total Input Cost</strong>. If your 10 input skins cost a combined $7.50, you need an expected return of at least $7.50 to break even. Any EV above $7.50 is profit; any EV below is a loss.</p>
<p>When accounting for Steam Market fees (15%), the breakeven becomes: <strong>Breakeven Listing Price = Total Input Cost / 0.87</strong>. For $7.50 in inputs, you need outputs with a total expected listing value of at least $8.62 to break even after fees.</p>

